&lt;li&gt;Assists in providing on-the-job training as required for new and existing employees.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains project files and appropriate records of work, compliant with company and aerospace industry standards, practices, and regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meets all company timelines, processes, trainings, and initiatives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you Need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor of Science Degree in Electrical, Mechanical, or Aerospace Engineering or equivalent field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong skills with MATLAB/Simulink, Python, or equivalent. Working knowledge of C/C++ a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with stability and control system design and assessment and/or vehicle flight modeling and simulation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in the aerospace industry required. UAS / UAM experience a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience assessing vehicle performance, flying, and handling qualities and related system performance.&lt;/li&gt;
